Deputy National Security Advisor Daleep Singh visited New Delhi to discuss deepening U.S.-India economic cooperation and addressing the economic impacts of Russia's war against Ukraine. Singh met with several Indian officials, including Principal Secretary P.K. Mishra, Minister of Commerce Piyush Goyal, and Foreign Secretary Harsh V. Shringla, among others. The discussions focused on U.S. sanctions imposed on Russia, cooperation on global food insecurity and energy prices, and the development of an Indo-Pacific Economic Framework. Both sides expressed commitment to continuing their close consultations.